#MEM id=acceptance-criteria source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/custom/acceptance-criteria/SKILL.md savings=11%
M||tx|---
M||name|acceptance-criteria
M||desc|dn's AC writing standard — absorbed from Priya (PM). Defines the binary pass/fail format qn uses for QA sign-off. Covers AC structure, definition of done, edge case coverage, and the pre-bd AC rv gate.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|dn absorbed Priya's PM responsibilities on 2026-04-01. Writing acceptance criteria is now dn's job. AC is the contract btw what gets built and what qn tests. Vague AC produces vague QA. This skill defines the format qn expects and dn must deliver.
M|Purp|**Ha|** qn does not start QA w/o written AC. dn does not hand off to dv/rj/mi w/o written AC. AC is written before implementation begins — never after.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|AC F|tx|Every AC item must be binary. A tester must be able to answer "did this pass?" w/ yes or no — no judgment calls.
M|AC F|tx|```
M|AC F|Feat|[feature name]
M|AC F|vt|[nz / hb / Both]
M|AC F|AC-0|[Binary condition — present tense, observable]
M|AC F|AC-0|[Binary condition]
M|AC F|AC-0|[Binary condition]
M|AC F|tx|...
M|AC F|Edge|
M|AC F|- AC|[Edge case condition]
M|AC F|- AC|[Edge case condition]
M|AC F|Defi|
M|AC F|it|[ ] All AC items pass
M|AC F|- [ |zero er
M|AC F|- [ |zero warnings
M|AC F|it|[ ] Tested on mobile viewport
M|AC F|it|[ ] Empty state handled
M|AC F|it|[ ] er state handled
M|AC F|it|[ ] Loading state handled
M|AC F|tx|```
M|AC F|tx|---
M|Writ|**Go|**
M|Writ|it|"When a us submits the form w/ an empty em field, an inline er message appears below the em input."
M|Writ|it|"The an dashboard loads within 3 seconds on a standard connection."
M|Writ|it|"Switching vt via the VentureSwitcher updates all dashboard data within one page reload."
M|Writ|**Ba|**
M|Writ|it|"The UI looks good" — not testable
M|Writ|it|"perf is acceptable" — no threshold
M|Writ|it|"The form works correctly" — too vague
M|Writ|**Ru|** If qn wld have to make a judgment call to determine pass/fail, rewrite the AC.
M|Writ|tx|---
M|1. F|tx|Every stated requirement from the task spec becomes at least one AC item.
M|2. A|it|"Unauthenticated request to [endpoint] returns 401."
M|2. A|it|"vt A us cannot access vt B data."
M|3. E|- Em|"When no data exists, the [cp] shows [specific empty state message]."
M|3. E|- Er|"When the ap returns an er, the [cp] shows [specific er message]."
M|3. E|- Lo|"While data is loading, a skeleton/spinner is displayed."
M|4. M|it|"The [feature] is fully functional at 375px viewport width."
M|4. M|tx|---
M|Pre-|Befo|
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Every AC item is binary — yes/no testable
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Every item in the task spec maps to at least one AC
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Auth/sec AC present (if applicable)
M|Pre-|- [ |empty, er, loading
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Mobile tested AC present
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Definition of Done checklist complete
M|Pre-|it|[ ] vt scope is explicit (nz / hb / Both)
M|Pre-|If a|rewrite before handoff. Never send ambiguous AC to dv — ambiguous AC is a bug factory.
M|Pre-|tx|---
M|Hand|When|
M|Hand|tx|```
M|Hand|Task|[task name]
M|Hand|vt|[scope]
M|Hand|DRI|[who builds it — rj / mi / both]
M|Hand|AC d|[paste full AC here]
M|Hand|Defi|[checklist]
M|Hand|Quin|starts when DRI marks READY FOR QA in chat
M|Hand|tx|```